    {
      "line": 54,
      "text": "Summer 1990"
    },
    {
      "line": 57,
      "text": "This issue never set out to have a theme. It began as*a serendipitous catch of all that flows"
    },
    {
      "line": 58,
      "text": "through the office, particularly of the many product, book, and catalog reviews piling up on our"
    },
    {
      "line": 59,
      "text": "shelves. Indeed, there are more reviews than usual in this issue. But it is only now, the last week"
    },
    {
      "line": 60,
      "text": "in production, that an alliance among the ideas on these pages has emerged. What vou have"
    },
    {
      "line": 61,
      "text": "here is an issue pointing to the reality of autonomous worlds. Virtual universes (p. 80). Man-"
    },
    {
      "line": 62,
      "text": "ufactured ecologies (p. 2). Artificial life (p. 20). Fabricated matter (p.104). Simulated history"
    },
    {
      "line": 64,
      "text": "(p. 118). All kinds of man-made designs that compete with the everyday world for our sense of"
    },
    {
      "line": 65,
      "text": "what is “real.” All kinds of worrisome worlds that seem to be acquiring their own minds and"
    },
    {
      "line": 66,
      "text": "momentum. All kinds of playing god. In short, welcome to the second Creation, the age of"
    },
    {
      "line": 69,
      "text": "Synthetic Realities."
